  "prompt": "What does add on item on Amazon mean?",
  "response": "An \"Add-on Item\" on Amazon refers to a product that is only available for purchase when your order meets a specific minimum purchase requirement, typically a total of $25 or more. This policy is designed to make shipping more economical for Amazon by encouraging customers to buy more items in a single order. Add-on items are usually lower-cost items, such as small household goods or personal care products. If your cart doesn't meet the minimum threshold, you won't be able to purchase the add-on item until you add more eligible products to your order.",
